In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1¼ cups water, and a pinch of
@salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook, covered, until
rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Wash and dry produce. Thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}(thinly sliced).

== Apricot-Chili Duck Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Apricot Jam{2%tablespoon}, @Sweet Thai Chili Sauce{2%ounce},
half the @Soy Sauce{1%tablespoon}, and 3 TBSP hot water. Set apricot-chili duck
sauce aside.

> Use 5 TBSP water for 4 servings.

== Pork ==

In a #large pan{}, heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{2%teaspoon} over medium-high heat.
Add @Ground Pork{10%ounce}, @Garlic Powder{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Using a #spatula{}, press into an even layer. Cook, without stirring,
until browned on bottom, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Break up meat into pieces and continue cooking until pork is cooked through,
~{1-2%minutes} more. Add half the apricot-chili duck sauce; cook, stirring
occasionally, until pork is glazed and coated, ~{1-3%minutes} more.

Turn off heat. Transfer pork to a #plate{}; tent with #foil{} until ready to serve.
Wipe out pan.

== Veggies ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add @Coleslaw Mix{4%ounce},
@Shredded Carrots{4%ounce}, and onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until tender
and browned, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add @Sesame Oil{1%tablespoon} and remaining @Soy Sauce{}. Cook, stirring, until
flavors meld, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} to taste.

== Assembly ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and stir in @Butter{1%tablespoon}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

> Use 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

Divide rice between #bowls{}; top with pork and veggies. Drizzle with remaining
apricot-chili duck sauce. Serve.

> Ground Pork is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.